The paper deals with the problem of computing maximal conditional expected accumulated rewards until reaching a target state in finite-state Markov decision processes. This problem is related to probabilistic programming and worst-case analysis, which are topics commonly studied in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and programming languages (cs.PL) sub-categories. The paper also presents algorithms for solving the problem, which involves computational complexity and optimization, topics that are relevant to the data structures (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), and control systems (cs.SY) sub-categories.
